# Cursor Rules — agent-workspace (core)

This repository is `agent-workspace`: a coordinator-driven AI workflow workspace, not an application repository.

Application repositories are cloned under `services/<service-name>/`. User reference docs go under `inputs/`.

> See also: `agent-workspace-source.mdc` (when editing `services/**` or `src/**`), `agent-workspace-runtime.mdc` (when editing `.runtime/**`), `agent-workspace-spec.mdc` (when editing `.agent/**`).

## Framework-template mode

When `.runtime/context/workflow-state.yaml` has `distribution_mode: framework-template` and `instance_status: not_applied`, this repo is the reusable framework distribution. `NEED_ONBOARDING`, empty service catalogs, and seed brain values are expected and must not block framework maintenance.

For changes confined to framework docs, rules, templates, workflow agents, commands, tool adapters, or helper scripts:

- classify `target_scope: framework`
- set `requires_onboarding: false`
- read only entrypoints and directly relevant framework files
- use lightweight fast-track evidence for trivial changes

Require onboarding only before analyzing or coding application source under `services/<service-name>/`.

## Read First

- `AGENTS.md`
- `CLAUDE.md`
- `COMMAND.md`
- `.agent/workflow.md`
- `.runtime/context/workflow-state.yaml`

## Core workflow rules (always)

- Route every natural-language request through `/coord`.
- Classify `target_scope` before broad brain/service reads.
- Use signature-first context loading before broad source reads: memory index, project/service profile summaries, context hints, then specific evidence files.
- Use `.runtime/context/model-routing.yaml` for agent model profiles and `.runtime/context/agent-activity.yaml` for `/status` activity/ETA/token/cost reporting.
- Switch models through `.runtime/context/model-routing.yaml.model_overrides`; do not edit agent files or remove stable profiles to switch models.
- Use `.runtime/context/response-ui.yaml` for markdown/text response structure.
- Use `python3 scripts/status-dashboard.py --mode <compact|concise|dashboard|models|json>` as a terminal status mirror when project slash commands are not exposed. Add `--write` to generate `.runtime/status.md` and `.runtime/status.html`.
- Use `python3 scripts/agent-activity.py` for adapter telemetry updates and `python3 scripts/architecture-health-check.py --strict` for optional deterministic drift checks.
- For applied-service tasks, require `task-analysis.yaml.context_plan` before implementation planning or coding.
- Do not jump directly to workflow agents or generated coders from raw user input.
- Specialist advisors live under `.claude/agents/specialists/<category>/` (19 advisor-only experts). Invoke them in-pipeline per `R-016` and `task-analysis.yaml.advisory_required`; they only write `.runtime/tasks/<task_id>/advisories/<id>.yaml`, never application code, never assign coders or mark gates, and are never a raw-user entrypoint.
- Cursor enforces source/secret/destructive gates via `.cursor/hooks/*` (parity with the Claude `scripts/hooks/*` guards; see `R-017`). Do not weaken or bypass these hooks; resolve the underlying rule instead.
- If a required fact is missing, mark `unknown`, cite the evidence gap, and ask through Coordinator. Do not fabricate.
- Claims of "done" must include evidence (file path, command output, or artifact).
- Do not fabricate exact token/cost/ETA. Use `unknown` or clearly marked estimates when Cursor does not expose reliable metrics.

## Task Folder Contract

Task IDs use `TASK-YYYYMMDD-NNN-slug`.

All task artifacts stay in `.runtime/tasks/<task_id>/`.

Required baseline artifacts for applied-service implementation tasks:

- `task-input.md`
- `task.yaml`
- `task-updates.yaml`
- `task-analysis.yaml`

Implementation/QC artifacts are created only by the matching workflow phase:

- `architecture-review.yaml`
- `implementation-plan.yaml`
- `service-assignments.yaml`
- `coder-results.yaml`
- `dev-verification.yaml`
- `qc-handoff.md`
- `qc-test-results.yaml`
- `qc-delivery-report.md`
- `bugs.yaml`
- `memory-updates.yaml`

The canonical Dev-to-QC handoff is `.runtime/tasks/<task_id>/qc-handoff.md`.

## Commands

Use `COMMAND.md` for the canonical command list. Start with `/coord` unless the user intentionally invokes a specific command.

## Anti-Guessing

If a required fact is missing, use `unknown`, state the evidence gap, and ask through Coordinator. Do not fabricate project facts.
